company information  bloomberg july    pm et capital markets company overview of halifax capital partners ii lp snapshot people company overview halifax capital partners ii lp specializes in management buyout growth capital industry consolidation and special situation transactions it prefers to invest in lower middlemarket and small private companies engaged in the infrastructure health and wellness sectors with an emphasis on consumer products and services the fund typically invests in soil preparation services veterinary services for livestock veterinary services specialties animal services farm labor and management services lawn and garden services ornamental shrub and tree services oil and gas field services bridge tunnel and elevated highway construction water sewer and pipeline construction electrical  halifax capital partners ii lp specializes in management buyout growth capital industry consolidation and special situation transactions it prefers to invest in lower middlemarket and small private companies engaged in the infrastructure health and wellness sectors with an emphasis on consumer products and services the fund typically invests in soil preparation services veterinary services for livestock veterinary services specialties animal services farm labor and management services lawn and garden services ornamental shrub and tree services oil and gas field services bridge tunnel and elevated highway construction water sewer and pipeline construction electrical work wrecking and demolition work specialty contract work pharmaceutical products in vivo diagnostic substances plastic plumbing pipes plastic products aerospace and defense transportation medical equipment surgical sets and instruments dental care equipment railroad switching and terminal establishments transportation infrastructure farm product warehousing and storage refrigerated warehousing and storage warehousing and storage road transportation of freight it also seeks to invest in marine cargo services marine ports and services airports and airport terminal services air freight and logistics services incidental to road transportation of freight sewage treatment systems refuse systems sanitary services healthcare equipment distribution food distribution alcoholic beverage distribution restaurants court reporting services commercial extermination and pest control commercial building care and improvement services healthcare equipment temporary help supply commercial security and safety services office services and supplies commercial repair services sports services medical doctor specialist services dental services medical doctor specialist and chiropractic services optometry services healthcare providers specialist services assisted living facilities and services hospitals and healthcare centers psychiatric hospital services hospitals and healthcare centers medical research laboratory services dental laboratory services home healthcare services kidney dialysis centers healthcare facilities healthcare providers and services junior colleges and technical institutes vocational schools schools child day care services testing laboratories facilities support management services diversified commercial and professional services and environmental and facilities services depending on the opportunity the fund also seeks investments in other fragmented industries of companies based in the united states it typically makes initial equity investments between  million and  million in companies with an enterprise value between  million and  million and an ebitda between  million and  million over a period of a year the fund prefer to have majority stake detailed description  connecticut avenue nwsuite washington dc united statesfounded in  phone  fax  key executives for halifax capital partners ii lp mr david w dupree managing director and chief executive officer age  mr kenneth m doyle cpa senior partner mr brent d williams senior partner compensation as of fiscal year  sim